Nested SQL Functions

A nested SQL query in Data Cloud is a query in another SQL query that’s embedded in a WHERE clause.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience

A subquery is used to return data in the original query as a condition so that you can restrict which data to retrieve.

EXAMPLE
SELECT
avg(SalesOrder__dlm.GrandTotalAmount__c) as avg__c,
SubQuery1.Id as customer_id__c
from SalesOrder__dlm 
JOIN (select Individual__dlm.Id__c as Id from Individual__dlm 
where year(Individual__dlm.BirthDate__c) > 1980)  as SubQuery1
on SalesOrder__dlm.SoldToCustomerId__c = SubQuery1.Id
group by 
customer_id__c;
